1
00:00:02,860 --> 00:00:10,850
This is a Live set powered by Fadercraft Control.

2
00:00:10,850 --> 00:00:13,260
Fourteen channels. Six controls each.

3
00:00:13,260 --> 00:00:18,580
Instant access throughout your project.

4
00:00:18,580 --> 00:00:20,600
The whole set sits on two pages.

5
00:00:20,600 --> 00:00:24,080
Hold to peek at the other page
and release to return.

6
00:00:24,080 --> 00:00:27,120
Turn the encoder to switch and stay.

7
00:00:27,120 --> 00:00:30,320
The same interaction pattern
carries across every channel.

8
00:00:30,320 --> 00:00:34,320
Each channel gives you six controls
across two encoder banks.

9
00:00:34,320 --> 00:00:37,400
Hold to peek at the other bank
and release to return.

10
00:00:37,400 --> 00:00:41,440
Turn the encoder to switch and stay.

11
00:00:41,440 --> 00:00:43,960
You've been mixing. Now play.

12
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:46,840
One button drops you into the last
instrument you touched,

13
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:48,200
right where you left it.

14
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:50,410
Press the button again,
and you're back to the mixer

15
00:00:50,410 --> 00:00:52,920
on the exact page you were working on.

16
00:00:52,920 --> 00:00:57,320
Your workflow stays uninterrupted.

17
00:00:57,320 --> 00:01:00,560
DAW Mixer and DAW Control
are always within reach.

18
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:04,720
Switch between native modes with a single
hotkey — or any key you assign.

19
00:01:04,720 --> 00:01:09,160
The same mapping concept carries
across pages, banks, and instrument jumps.

20
00:01:09,160 --> 00:01:14,120
You define how navigation works once,
and it stays consistent under your fingers.

21
00:01:14,120 --> 00:01:17,120
Everything adapts to your workflow.

22
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:20,950
14 channels. Six controls per channel.

23
00:01:20,950 --> 00:01:23,360
Designed for muscle memory.

24
00:01:23,360 --> 00:01:27,080
One workflow for production,
mixing, and live performance.

25
00:01:27,080 --> 00:01:30,120
This is Fadercraft Control XL.

26
00:01:30,120 --> 00:01:32,360
Stay in the music.
